OL,3,CHeathrow Airport releases iconic
OL,4,Cphotos to celebrate 80th anniversary
OL,6,FHeathrow Airport has released a number
OL,7,Fof images capturing some of its most
OL,8,Ficonic moments to celebrate 80 years
OL,9,Fsince first opening its doors.
OL,11,FThe airport - which today is the most
OL,12,Fconnected in the world - officially
OL,13,Fopened on March 25, 1946, under the
OL,14,Fname 'London Airport'.
OL,16,FA converted Lancaster bomber, called
OL,17,FStarlight, flew the first post-war
OL,18,Fflight from Heathrow, which took
OL,19,Fpassengers to Argentina's capital,
OL,20,FBuenos Aires.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
